<title>UK: HSBC surges to new peak on short squeeze.</title>
<headline>HSBC surges to new peak on short squeeze.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in HSBC Holdings surged to a record on Thursday on what dealers said was a technical short squeeze.</p>
<p>By 1241 GMT, the shares were up 49-1/2p, or 2.9 percent, to 1753-1/2, having climbed as high as 1757.  </p>
<p>Dealers said there were a couple of large buyers that ignited the initial advance.</p>
<p>&quot;There was a bit of a technical shortage in the market,&quot; said one dealer. &quot;Once the buying started, people just started chasing their tails try to close out their positions.&quot;</p>
<p>--London Newsroom +44 171 542 5106</p>
